commentary: The year 1972 was overwhelming to the book lovers as they sensed there seemed to be a chance of opening up.

Bei Dao mentions that before the rustication, they have already started to read extensively. First, under the influence of his classmates he read books on politics, economics and history, in order to devote his life to the revolution. After he became a builder, he started to be interested in the literary works. At that time, the most popular books were the neibu books, namely yellow-covered books. Sartre's Novel was among the most influential for Bei Dao.

The text is about the author's experience when he was a student at the Beijing No. 4 High School. He encountered the May 16 Notification and took part in the Red guards, raging the campus and households.
The text is about the time before the CR when the author was Huang Yongsheng's secretary. He commented on Huang Yongsheng and wrote some impressions.
